adjectives.description: jake (comparative more jake, superlative most jake)

examples: ‘What do you care? Just keep your nose clean and everything will be jake.’

entries.meaning: (New York, MTE, MLE, slang) police, a federal government officer.
(slang) A police officer, a cop (on foot, rather than in a patrol car).
A Discordian prank involving a large number of people sending bizarre letters or parcels to a targeted individual.
examples: Hello, I'm afraid in some regards I'm too discordian for my own good and I forgot to either write down the jake-dupe's address, or include it in my repost when I suggested today as jake day....

verbs.description: jake (third-person singular simple present jakes, present participle jaking, simple past and past participle jaked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To play a Discordian prank on (somebody), involving a large number of people sending bizarre letters or parcels to that person.
